P(A) ≥ P(B)

Therefore, the correct answer is (a) Fred would likely deposit the money from the sale.

The conjunction fallacy arises because people tend to judge the probability of a conjunction based on how representative or plausible the combined scenario appears, rather than considering the individual probabilities of each event.
